    a: 'File IRS Form W-7, the "Application for IRS Individual Taxpayer Identification Number", with proof of identity and foreign status (a valid passport is the simplest option), usually alongside a federal tax return. You can submit by mail to the IRS, through an IRS-authorized Certifying Acceptance Agent (CAA), or in person at an IRS Taxpayer Assistance Center.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How long does it take to get an ITIN?',
