  },
  {
    q: 'What documents do I need for an ITIN application?',
    a: 'A completed Form W-7, proof of identity and foreign status, and usually a federal tax return. A valid passport is the only single document that proves both identity and foreign status. Without a passport, you need two alternative documents, such as a national ID plus a birth certificate.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does it cost money to get an ITIN?',
    a: 'The IRS charges no fee for Form W-7. Certifying Acceptance Agents and tax preparers may charge a fee for their services. You can apply directly by mail at no cost if you\'re comfortable mailing original or certified copies of your documents.',
