    q: 'Does my ITIN expire?',
    a: 'ITINs not used on a federal tax return for three consecutive tax years expire automatically. The IRS also periodically expires older ITINs issued before a certain year. If your ITIN has expired, you must renew it by filing Form W-7 before using it on a new return. Check IRS.gov for the current expiration schedule.',
